ex-bard, ex-EQ, currently bored <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukulanaesoulsease.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kulanae Soulsease</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#CC9900>(11/22/00 12:11:40 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.wwa.com/~danas/Kulanae4.jpg width=119 height=158></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on adjusted bard songs</span><hr size=1> Well hon I haven't really had a chance to play with Pixie yet and I don't as yet have SoT which is level 53.  But by all accounts SoT really rocks now.  It has made Bards a viable alternative to Chanters for crowd control.  The changes to the &quot;Jonthan's&quot; line have been less well received as they are self only.  Perhaps on the PvP servers Bards need these.  The only thing I can see them for is to try to duel other melee classes toe-to-toe and we would still get owned. <p><font size=2 face="Tempus Sans ITC, Verdana, Helvetica">
