<br>
<br>
A bards life... Run fast, die faster, leave a pretty corpse.


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukalsyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalsyre</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#CC9900>(11/22/00 4:35:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: =)</span><hr size=1> I have been using SoT exclusively.  I have done just a few tests at this time, but here is what I have.<br>
<br>
*  The song does not require an Instrument to sing.<br>
*  The song is wind based, but a magical flute shows no discernable difference.<br>
*  With a Charisma of 140 my SoT mes will last roughly 23 seconds.<br>
*  I have not tested the effect of CHA on SoT<br>
*  When messing blues, I get very low resist rates, maybe 1 out of 100 casts get resisted.<br>
*  This song requires no mana.<br>
*  Level cap is 55 or 56<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I have effectively and very easily been able to keep 4 high blue cons messed at one time with SoT.  5 is tough simply because of the need to re-target mobs, but it is feasible this could be done with practice.<br>
<br>
One nice thing is you can keep 2 mobs messed while still twisting 2 songs in for combat (I use cantana and celerity usally) and still be able to switch between the 2 messed mobs and the 1 mob you are engaged with for melee.<br>
<br>
Some applications I have discovered...<br>
<br>
SoT can be used to help the enchanter on first pull.  Often times an enchanter uses an AE mes on first pull which doesnt last very long.  While the enchanter is messing them 1 by 1 the AE mes start to break.  I have used SoT to give the enchanter those much needed extra seconds to get each mob messed with a target mes spell.<br>
<br>
SoT can be used toward the end of the fight.  Often times an enchaner may go OOM during a long fight, with a few mobs still left.  This is a perfect time for a Bard to take over since the bard's mes is mana free.<br>
<br>
SoT is also great for Kedge Keep.  Enchanters can find it difficult to keep steady enough underwater to cast a spell.  With Bard mes you are free to move as you are casting.<br>
<br>
A group without an enchanter can use a bard to do CC all by his or herself.  Since bards can keep up to 4 or even 5 mobs messed at once with SoT, they are often capable enough to handle most trains.<br>
<br>
Bard mes may be great for large raids.  Enchanters are usally OOM from buffing C2, Aug, Rune, for the big fight, and dont have alot of spare mana to keep mobs messed.  Again since bard mes is mana free, this is frees up the enchanters to buff.<br>
<br>
<br>
Tests I am still planning to run...<br>
<br>
Charisma effect on duration<br>
Charisma effect on resists<br>
