<br>
It seems good enough to actually use reliably, and when wanderers popped in it wasn't too much trouble to mez a 2nd or even a 3rd.  Trying to hold more than 3 is prolly not such a hot idea if you can help it, but given that we can cast on the run - it's vaguely tryable.<br>
<br>
Alanna <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquemnwyndrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quemn Wyndrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 134<br> <font color=#CC9900>(11/25/00 4:14:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   SoT</span><hr size=1> SoT works great, in sebilis and in karnor i have kept 2-4 mobs mezzed at a time, the wind instrument doesnt seem to effect it, but ive found charisma to work good:<br>
